General Commands
pwd - Print Working Directory
ls - List files and directories
cd - Change Directory
mkdir - Make Directory
rm - Remove files or directories
cp - Copy files or directories
mv - Move or rename files or directories
touch - Create an empty file or update the timestamp of an existing file
cat - Display the contents of a file
nano - Simple text editor
vim - Powerful text editor
less - View file contents one page at a time
uname -a - Display detailed information about the system
top - Display running processes and system usage
df -h - Show disk space usage
du -sh - Show directory space usage
free -h - Display memory usage

Networking and Security Commands
ping - Check connectivity to a host
ifconfig - Display network configuration (deprecated, use 'ip')
ip addr show - Show/manage network interfaces
netstat -tuln - Network statistics
nmap - Network scanner
wireshark - Network protocol analyzer
tcpdump - Network packet analyzer
ettercap - Network security tool for man-in-the-middle attacks
arpspoof - ARP spoofing tool
airmon-ng - Start monitor mode on wireless interfaces
airodump-ng - Capture raw 802.11 frames
aireplay-ng - Packet injection tool
aircrack-ng - Crack WEP and WPA-PSK keys
hydra - Password cracking tool
john - Password cracker
metasploit - Penetration testing framework
msfconsole - Console for Metasploit
exploit - Execute exploits in Metasploit
nikto - Web server scanner
sqlmap - Automated SQL injection tool
burpsuite - Web vulnerability scanner
zap - OWASP ZAP, web vulnerability scanner
msfvenom - Payload generator for Metasploit
setoolkit - Social Engineering Toolkit
wpscan - WordPress vulnerability scanner

System Information and Management
ps aux - Display running processes
kill - Terminate a process by ID
killall - Terminate all processes by name
service - Manage system services
systemctl - Control the systemd system and service manager
htop - Interactive process viewer
crontab - Schedule commands to run at specific times
uptime - Display how long the system has been running
whoami - Display the current logged-in user
hostname - Display or set the system's hostname
dmesg - Print kernel ring buffer messages
lshw - List hardware configurations
lsblk - List information about block devices
blkid - Display block device attributes

File Permissions and Ownership
chmod - Change file permissions
chown - Change file owner and group
chgrp - Change group ownership
umask - Set default file permissions

Disk and File Operations
fdisk - Partition table manipulator
mkfs - Create a filesystem
mount - Mount a filesystem
umount - Unmount a filesystem
dd - Convert and copy a file
tar - Archive files
gzip - Compress files
bzip2 - Compress files
apt-get - Package handling utility
apt - Advanced Package Tool interface
dpkg - Debian package manager

Scripting and Development
python - Python interpreter
perl - Perl interpreter
ruby - Ruby interpreter
gcc - GNU Compiler Collection
make - Build and compile projects

Miscellaneous Tools
gpg - GnuPG encryption tool
hashcat - Password cracking tool
netcat - Network utility for reading/writing data
socat - Network communication utility
wget - Download files from the web
curl - Transfer data from or to a server
scp - Secure copy (remote file copy program)
ssh - Secure shell for remote login
ftp - File Transfer Protocol client
telnet - User interface to the TELNET protocol

